# Urazovo, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Urazovo (; , Ura≈∫) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Urazovsky Selsoviet, Uchalinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 1,051 as of 2010. There are 19 streets.
Geography
Urazovo is located 22&nbsp;km southwest of Uchaly (the district's administrative centre) by road.
